… dynamic web applications backed by SQL databases. … well-typed Ur/Web programs
“don’t go wrong” in a very broad sense. Not only do they not crash during particular
page generations, but they also may not:
• Suffer from any kinds of code-injection attacks
• Have mismatches between HTML forms and the fields expected by their handlers
• Include client-side code that makes incorrect assumptions about the “AJAX”-style
services that the remote web server provides
• Use improper marshaling or unmarshaling in communication with SQL databases
or between browsers and web servers
